OL,3,CZookeepers support injured monkeys in
OL,4,CKenya as part of conservation work
OL,6,FCredit: Drusillas Conservation and
OL,7,FColobus Conservation
OL,9,FTwo keepers from a wildlife park in
OL,10,FSussex have spent two weeks doing
OL,11,Fmonkey conservation work in Kenya,
OL,12,Fincluding building bridges to protect
OL,13,Fthem from dangerous power lines.
OL,15,FZookeeper Emily Robinson and Zoo
OL,16,FSection Leader Sam Kenward, both from
OL,17,FDrusillas near Alfriston, travelled to
OL,18,Fthe Kenyan coast to work alongside the
OL,19,FColobus Conservation team, which
OL,20,Frescues and rehabilitates injured,
OL,21,Fsick and displaced primates.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/7
